<p><strong>The Seminar offers:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>Photography and video workshops led by some of the country’s most talented photojournalists, aimed at helping photographers of any skill level.</li>
  <li>Distinguished speakers from photojournalism field.</li>
  <li>Vendor displays of the latest photography and video gear.</li>
  <li>Free clean and checks of equipment (limit two), provided by Nikon and Canon.</li>
  <li>Photography contest, awarding more than $5,000 in prizes.</li>
  <li>Portfolio reviews.</li>
</ul>

<p>Speakers throughout the years have included Pulitzer Prize winners, Photographer of the Year winners, major magazine and wire service photographers, influential directors of photography, important educators in photojournalism, academia.</p>

<p>The Seminar runs for two days. Friday workshops, are smaller, more interactive and more topic-driven. Saturday Speakers bring all our attendees together for Speaker talks. Portfolio reviews are available both nights. The Seminar is open to all attendees. You will find a mix of pros, students, teachers and enthusiasts.</p>